1          /*------------------------------------------------------------------*
2          | MACRO NAME  : data_specs_cli20260320
3          | SHORT DESC  : Creates a specifications document on a library of
4          |               datasets with CLI parameter support
5          *------------------------------------------------------------------*
6          | CREATED BY  : Modified for CLI usage
7          | ORIGINAL    : Meyers, Jeffrey (07/28/2016)
8          *------------------------------------------------------------------*
9          | VERSION UPDATES:
10         | 2026-03-20: Extended SYSPARM to support optional macro parameters
11         |   - Optional params passed as key=value pairs after output dir
12         | 2025-01-21: Modified to accept CLI parameters via SYSPARM
13         |   - Added input/output path parsing from SYSPARM
14         |   - Added automatic creation of DAC_Documents folder
15         |   - Added path validation
16         | See original data_specs macro for prior version history.
17         *------------------------------------------------------------------*
18         | PURPOSE
19         | Create a data specifications sheet for all datasets in a
20         | designated directory with CLI parameter support for automated
21         | workflows. Allows for a quick look at the data within a library
22         | or allows for a simple data dictionary to be built.
23         | The macro outputs a report with three types of tables. The first
24         | is a listing of the datasets included in the library along with
25         | the number of rows, number of unique indexes, and number of
26         | variables. The second table shows the number of variables that
27         | exist across multiple datasets along with any different labels
28         | given to them. The last type of table is built for each dataset
29         | on a separate tab listing the variables and specs (label, format,
30         | and values) for each.
31         |
32         | 1.0: REQUIRED SYSPARM PARAMETERS (pipe-delimited)
2                                           The SAS System                16:55 Friday, March 20, 2026

33         | INPUT_DIRECTORY  = Path to the folder containing SAS datasets
34         |                    (.sas7bdat) to be summarized
35         | OUTPUT_DIRECTORY = Path to the folder where the DAC_Documents
36         |                    subfolder and output file will be created.
37         |                    Must exist prior to execution.
38         |
39         | 2.0: OPTIONAL SYSPARM PARAMETERS (pipe-delimited key=value pairs)
40         | INDEX         = Allows the designation of multiple index variables
41         |                 to determine number of patients or other interest
42         |                 within a dataset.
43         | CAT_THRESHOLD = Determines the number of variable levels that can
44         |                 exist before the program will not output the
45         |                 frequency and percentage of each level. If a
46         |                 numeric variable exceeds this many levels then
47         |                 distribution statistics will be used instead.
48         |                 Must be greater than or equal to 0. Default: 10.
49         | FORMAT        = For the summary of individual datasets this
50         |                 determines if the variables will be listed in
51         |                 CONDENSED (one row per variable), LONG (one
52         |                 column), or WIDE (one row) format. Options are
53         |                 LONG, CONDENSED, and WIDE. Default is LONG.
54         | ORDER         = Determines how the variables will be ordered in
55         |                 the dataset summary tabs. VARNUM will order by
56         |                 the variable order in the dataset and NAME will
57         |                 order alphabetically. Options are VARNUM and NAME.
58         |                 Default is VARNUM.
59         | WHERE         = Allows a WHERE clause to be used on the dictionary
60         |                 table to subset the datasets included.
61         | DEBUG         = Determines if notes are on/off and if temporary
62         |                 datasets are cleaned up. Options are 0 (no notes,
63         |                 datasets cleaned up) and 1 (notes shown, datasets
64         |                 left behind). Default is 0.
65         |
66         | USAGE:
67         |   sas -sysparm "input_directory|output_directory[|key=value|...]"
68         |       -sysin data_specs_cli20260320.sas
69         |
70         | OUTPUT STRUCTURE:
71         |   output_directory\
72         |   └── DAC_Documents\
73         |       └── data_specs_<libname>_<YYYYMMDD>.xlsx
74         |           (summary sheet + one sheet per dataset)
75         *------------------------------------------------------------------*
76         | OPERATING SYSTEM COMPATIBILITY
77         | SAS v9.4 or Higher: Yes
78         *------------------------------------------------------------------*
79         | MACRO CALL
80         |
81         | Not applicable. Script is invoked directly via the SAS command
82         | line using -sysin and -sysparm. Optional parameters are passed
83         | as pipe-delimited key=value pairs within SYSPARM.
84         |
85         | Equivalent direct macro call (for reference):
86         |   %data_specs_cli(
3                                           The SAS System                16:55 Friday, March 20, 2026

87         |       index=,
88         |       cat_threshold=10,
89         |       where=,
90         |       format=long,
91         |       order=varnum,
92         |       debug=0
93         |   );
94         *------------------------------------------------------------------*
95         | EXAMPLES
96         |
97         | Basic usage (default options):
98         |   sas -sysparm "C:\data\input|C:\data\output"
99         |       -sysin data_specs_cli20260320.sas
100        |
101        | Wide format, alphabetical variable order:
102        |   sas -sysparm "C:\data\input|C:\data\output|format=wide|order=name"
103        |       -sysin data_specs_cli20260320.sas
104        |
105        | With index variable and custom category threshold:
106        |   sas -sysparm "C:\data\input|C:\data\output|index=USUBJID|cat_threshold=5"
